Load topography and roads and rasterize roads

## PNF.asc has GDAL driver AAIGrid 
## and has 250 rows and 434 columns
## topomap.asc has GDAL driver AAIGrid 
## and has 103 rows and 151 columns
## OGR data source with driver: ESRI Shapefile 
## Source: "C:/Users/usuario/Bats_California/layers", layer: "Roads"
## with 4127 features
## It has 22 fields
split<-raster(speed2)
plot(split)

res(split)
## [1] 0.003810748 0.003810748
writeRaster(split, filename="speed.asc", format="ascii")
